			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4522591">
									

<p>I actually started from Mark's playthroughs. I thought it was just some random horror game and didn't really pay much attention to it. Then I went on to Tat's SCP interview logs, during a search for every SCP in CB, which made me kind of interested in what &quot;SCP&quot; really is. So I went on to the site and saw this very highly classified theme that composes the webpage and I went like &quot;holy shit this is scary in a realistic way&quot;. I went on to read Series I first because 1.) I thought there is some sort of order that you have to go through and 2.) I thought it has some lore significance. Though all of that didn't really gave me the kick to join the site. (Also because there was some school needing to be done)</p>
<p>What really pushed me is discovering the over simplified manga and seeing how ideas forum crit was going on. First of, the manga. It really showed me what the site had in store and some of which I passed through while scrolling Series I (critical tomatoes, Leviathan, 343, etc.). That was the time that made me check out the site as a whole. I went out and about browsing the User Resources and SCP Community tabs on the side bar and that's when I discovered the forums. I checked it out and saw a lot of ideas coming from promising writers.</p>
<p>Because I don't have an account at the time, I couldn't give my own opinion and critique on their concepts. Along with that, I saw ideas having mistakes in their ideas/posts like, thing that does a thing, generic item, not enough details/explanation, and the occasional sandbox link being the only content. That is what made me want to join the site, to voice my opinion, provide critique on their work and teach users on how to use the forums. (And occasionally read/write something)</p>
