<p>My origin story is a tad embarrassing. Back in the sixth grade or so, I was getting really into creepypasta stuff and found a &quot;documentary&quot; on YouTube about Slenderman. <a href="/scp-582">SCP-582</a> was specifically referenced as a potential representation of Slendy and I checked out the site.</p>
<p>If memory serves I attempted to read through Series I, but I, like… thought it was real? Or thought there was a risk it was. So I avoided SCP-001 and refused to open collapsible blocks that said &quot;Level X Clearance Required&quot;. That led to a very surface-Level engagement with the site and I eventually dropped it.</p>
<p>Fast-forward to a year-and-a-half ago when I saw <a href="https://youtu.be/eRjnPwoxSWU">a collab video between Internet Historian and TheVolgun</a>, which in turn led to the Confinement series, which in turn led to reading more articles; as in actually reading them this time.</p>
<p>I read <a href="/scp-1730">SCP-1730</a> and now I'm an author I guess</p>

